<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E5BFFD648A7519FFE2BFF5F" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E5BFFD548A7519FFD8FF81C" blockId="21.[151,1437,1715,2028]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E5BFFD548A7519FFE02F93C" bold="true" box="[151,423,1715,1740]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E5BFFD54A995198FCA1F93B" box="[681,772,1716,1740]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. Head black-brown, except mandible, clypeus and anterior half of face testaceous; ventral region of head black; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma black-brown; legs testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 8.5:6:9:9.5:10:9.5:8:7:8:11; antennal segment 9 less than twice as long as broad (8:5). Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; POL = 10; OL = 7; OOL = 11.5; OPL = 7; TL = 5. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, granulated. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.75 length of scutum. Propodeum with transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; dorsal surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels, lateral areas rugose and median area smooth. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E58FFD648F757B4FE2BFF5F" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,356]" box="[199,398,151,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E58FFD648F757B4FEAEFF40" bold="true" box="[199,267,152,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
